    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You can spend <strong>inspiration</strong> to reroll any d20 roll made by yourself, another player, or the GM after the roll has been made.</p><p>You may also spend inspiration to activate a <strong>flashback</strong> with a reaction on your turn. The GM sets the <strong>flashback cost</strong> when you activate a flashback, which costs a number of inspiration points based on its complexity. Other players may also donate inspiration points to you.</p><ul><li><strong>1 point - An ordinary action for which you had easy opportunity.</strong> The rogue persuaded her friend Chael to agree to arrive at the dice game ahead of time, to suddenly spring out as a surprise ally.</li><li><strong>2 points</strong> - <strong>A complex action or unlikely opportunity.</strong> The ranger hid his pistols into a hiding spot near the card table so he could retrieve them after the pat-down at the front door.</li><li><strong>3+ points</strong> - <strong>An elaborate action that involved special opportunities or contingencies.</strong> The wizard has already studied the history of the property and learned of a ghost that is known to haunt the sewers leading into the basementâ€”a ghost that can be compelled to reveal the location of the hidden vault.</li></ul>",
